context: 30681,What's better than eating good food you asked? How about eating good food with good friends!!! A few of my friends wanted to join in on the search for a good PHILLY CHEESESTEAK sandwich and we started with Woody's because they are open late. I ordered their PHILLY CHEESTEAK with onions along with some chips and a cold and crisp coke. The sandwich itself felt a bit dry and I wished it had more cheese. The bread is good but a bit too thick for my taste, taking a big bite will need to be followed by a sip of that cold and delicious coca-cola. Now, here is the good about the place... the meat itself is very tasty and they are very generous with the amount of meat you get on your sandwich. You have a COCA-COLA fountain you can get up and self serve yourself some refills if needed. Although the place is small and has limited parking, I don't see parking being a problem because there is parking all around the surrounding area. There are plenty of tables inside and out to sit at so if you're by yourself or with a larger group, you can find the right table. The place is open until midnight on Sun-Thu and open until 4AM on Fri and Sat which is great!!!! You always have to think "how much did I get for my money" and for a $7 sandwich, Woody's is definitely a spot to stop by if you're hungry, in the area and it's late.
